The paper discusses the design of deep neural networks using numerical differential equations, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of numerical analysis in designing effective deep architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) category. The paper also presents results on image classification tasks, which suggests that it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of stochastic control and stochastic training, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY) categories, respectively.
